full_text: Contact Manager is the system of record for vendors. ClaimCenter allows users to create vendors, but they are stored in, and linked to, Contact Manager. Vendors created or modified from ClaimCenter require approval from Contact Manager. Andy Applegate logs into ClaimCenter. He is working on the Andrew Williams claim. Andy learns that the vendor that he chose for the claim, Meineke Car Care Center, is not able to take Mr. Williams' call. He goes to the car. He goes to parties involved. Since he is not going to use Meineke, he selects it. And clicks Delete. This simply removes the vendor from a relationship to this claim, it does not delete the vendor from the system of record, Contact Manager. Andy found a vendor that can repair Mr. Williams' car, but the vendor is not in the system. Since Andy thinks this vendor may be able to do the work and that it could prove useful later, he creates the vendor that can repair Mr. Williams' car, but the vendor is not in the system. Since Andy thinks this vendor may be able to do the work and that it could prove useful later, it's the vendor. The name of the vendor is Bill's Quick Auto Repair. The shop is located on Beamer Road in San Mateo, California. He has heard that the shop is not easy to find, so he adds that note to the vendor record. Like any parties involved, vendors need at least one rule to be related to a claim. Bill's Quick Auto Repair is going to be the repair shop for Mr. Williams' car, so he selects the Ford and sets the rule to repair shop. He also wants to set Bill's Quick Auto Repair as a service vendor for the claim. So he accepts the default related to, which is the claim, and selects service vendor as the role. He clicks Update to save the new vendor. The update adds the vendor to Claim Center and Contact Manager, as indicated by the linked message. However, although it is in sync, the contact is pending approval. Vendors created in Claim Center have a pending status until approved in Contact Manager. Carla Clark is the vendor manager for Succeed Insurance. She logs into Contact Manager to check for any vendors that have been changed or added from Claim Center. On the opening screen, she sees that there is one pending change. There are two tabs on the Pending Changes screen, one for Updates and one for Creates. The Updates tab shows that there are no updates that need approval. The Create tab shows that there is one Create action that needs to be approved. This is a new vendor created from Claim Center or another core product. Carla clicks the Create tab. Carla sees that the pending vendor is Bill's Quick Auto Repair. She looks at the details and although they are not very complete, she decides to approve the vendor creation. She clicks Approve to approve the new vendor. Meanwhile, back in Claim Center, Andy is still logged in, and has not moved off of the Contact screen. He refreshes the Contact record by selecting any other contact. And then clicks Bill's Quick Auto Repair. After the Contact is Refreshed, the Sync Message shows that the Contact is linked to the Address Book and is in Sync. Recall that earlier it was linked but not in Sync. Once Carla approved the new vendor, the contract was automatically flagged as in Sync in Claim Center. Next, we look at what happens when a vendor is changed in Contact Manager. Carla opens the Search screen. She enters Bill as the company name and clicks Search. Carla clicks Bill's Quick Auto Repair. She looks at the vendor details. The location description is not something she wants on a vendor record. So she edits the contact. Carla deletes the location description. Carla clicks Update to save the changes to the vendor record. She sees that the location description is now Blink in Contact Manager. Just as before, back in Claim Center, Andy is still logged in and is still on the Contact screen. To refresh the vendor contact, Andy clicks on any other contact. He then clicks Bill's Quick Auto Repair. Andy notices two things. First, that the contact is linked to Address Book and is in Sync. Secondly, he sees that the location description is now Blank. That's because Carla, the vendor manager for Succeed Insurance, removed the location description from the contact. This ends the Adding Contacts in Claim Center demonstration.
